161
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:20,083
No, actually,
it's short for Natasha.

162
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:22,449
Natasha.

163
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:25,216
What kind of a name
is Chance?

164
00:20:25,324 --> 00:20:28,623
Well, my mama took one.

165
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:33,355
So how did you lose
your papa?

166
00:20:35,634 --> 00:20:40,094
My parents, um, they got divorced
when I was seven and my father...

167
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,639
Well, he moved away.

168
00:20:45,644 --> 00:20:49,546
We started to write and
he even called me a couple of times.

169
00:20:49,648 --> 00:20:52,674
Three weeks ago
the letters just stopped.

170
00:20:56,488 --> 00:20:59,423
I've got a friend here
who can help us.

171
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:03,050
You check the line,
I'll look around inside.

172
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:15,800
Hey, you don't have
a bottle of hot sauce on ya, do ya?

173
00:21:15,907 --> 00:21:18,102
- Elijah. What's happening?
- Hi.

174
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:20,110
Wednesday meat loaf.

175
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:22,544
I mean, they said
it was meat loaf.

176
00:21:22,648 --> 00:21:26,448
- I thought you were gonna get a ship.
- I lost my boarding pass.

177
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:31,849
I've got something
to show you.

178
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:33,857
You two know each other?

179
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:37,895
- We met yesterday.
Have you seen my father?
- I saw the next best thing.

180
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,964
I was over at
Plaza D'ltalia yesterday...

181
00:21:40,065 --> 00:21:43,091
and I saw this sleeping bag
in a cart.

182
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:48,138
It was a tiger stripe, like the kind
they used to issue to Recon guys.

183
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,538
Your daddy had one
just like it.

184
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:54,110
- Thanks, Charlie.
- You bet.

185
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:54,228
Don't be offended.
He passed them out for money.

186
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:57,536
Uh, yeah, I've had to
do it myself.

187
00:23:02,647 --> 00:23:04,547
Here. Barracks Street.

188
